        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 6 1874</date>
                    <salute>My dear Bates</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Will you be so kind as to send me, addressed “<hi rend="underline">to Orpington Station</hi> <hi rend="underline">Kent S.E.R.</hi>”, the following books which I find in your catalogue.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>“Jarves. Hist. of the Sandwich I’s”<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>“Ellis Narrative, with remarks on S.I.”<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>(N.B. please to observe whether S.I. means Sandwich I.s, for Polynesian researches are here entered on y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> catalogue by mistake)<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p> 

    <table>
        <row>
            <cell rend="left">“Simpson— The Sandwich I.s”</cell>
            <cell rows="2"><hi rend="stretchyVertical">}</hi></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell rend="left">&amp; Progress of events”. )<ref target="#foot.f5"/></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell rend="left">“Cheever— Life in the Sandwich I.s”<ref target="#foot.f6"/></cell>
            <cell/>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell rend="left">“Hill— Travels to the S.I.”<ref target="#foot.f7"/></cell>
            <cell/>
        </row>
    </table>
 
<p>This makes 5 books, &amp; I do not know whether you can stretch your power so as to lend me so many; but do if you can, &amp; they shall be returned soon—</p>
<p>yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>I want to hunt for history of Infanticide in Sandwich Isl<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. &amp; for population returns.— I have now met with those quoted, but I want the originals.—</p>
<p>P.S. Do I not owe the Society the price of the Classed Catalogue of Books?—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 <hi rend="italic">Kent</hi>] <hi rend="italic">interl in CD’s hand</hi> </note>
